title: Executive Order 8336-Revocation of Executive Order No. 3355 of November 19, 1920, Withdrawing Land for Use as an Administrative Site
content: By virtue of the authority vested in me by the act of June 25, 1910, c. 421, 36 Stat. 847, Executive Order No. 3355 of November 19, 1920, temporarily withdrawing certain lands in Alaska for use by the Forest Service as a dock site in connection with the administration of the Chugach National Forest, is hereby revoked.
citation: Franklin D. Roosevelt, Executive Order 8336-Revocation of Executive Order No. 3355 of November 19, 1920, Withdrawing Land for Use as an Administrative Site Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/371927
